8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 394, L.D. 626, “An Act to Explicitly
10 Allow the Department of Corrections to Charge Room and Board to Residents Who
11 Perform Remote Work in Detention and Correctional Facilities and to Amend the Laws
12 Governing Rehabilitative Programs”
13 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
14 'An Act to Remove the Explicit Authority of the Department of Corrections to Charge
15 Room and Board to Residents Who Participate in Work Release or Remote Work in
16 Detention and Correctional Facilities'
17 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1 by striking out all of paragraph E (page 1,
18 lines 28 to 35 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
19 'E. Every client participating in the work release program is liable for the cost of board
20 in the facility.
21 (1) The reasonable cost of board for a client in a facility is fixed by the
22 commissioner. In fixing the reasonable cost of the board to be paid, the
23 commissioner shall take into consideration other state laws or judicial
24 determinations that affect the client's income.
25 (2) Funds received from clients for the board must be placed in the General Fund.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, changes the title of the
3300 bill. It removes the bill's addition that a resident in a Department of Corrections
3311 correctional or detention facility participating in remote work is liable for the cost of room
